b) the term "C1 -C4 alkoxy" refers to a branched or straight chained alkoxy radical containing from 1-4 carbon atoms, such as methoxy, ethoxy, n-propoxy, isopropoxy, n-butoxy, isobutoxy, and the like;


c) the term "halogen" refers to a fluorine atom, a chlorine atom, a bromine atom, or a iodine atom;


